        <num>CC 1819</num>
        <heading>1819.  Effect of indivisible obligation among successors</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1819.  Effect of indivisible obligation among successors
An indivisible obligation may not be divided among the successors of the obligor or of the obligee, who are thus subject to the rules governing solidary obligors or solidary obligees.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109057</p>
